21/10/2004
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, who also currently holds the post of OSCE chairman-in-office, opened a Bulgarian consulate in Podgorica during his visit Wednesday (20 October).
Passy and Montenegrin counterpart Miodrag Vlahovic also sealed a protocol for co-operation between the two ministries.
Following talks with Vlahovic, President Filip Vujanovic and Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic, Passy said Montenegro's progress in the reform process was "obvious".
(Bulgarian Foreign Ministry Web site, Tanjug - 20/10/04)
